<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--Poland-Potatoes     12-15 0160</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Poland-Potatoes,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Idahoans Sending Potato Farming Equipment to Poland</HEAD>
<DATELINE>IDAHO FALLS, Idaho (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Idahoans are sending potato farming
gear to Poland in a gesture of support for the democratic movement
in eastern Europe, a congressman said.
   About 30 pieces of equipment, including potato diggers and
planters, will be sent initially, Democratic Rep. Richard Stallings
said, noting the spud is as central to Polish agriculture as it is
to farming in Idaho, the nation's biggest potato grower.
   ``We are witnessing events in Eastern Europe of historic
proportions, and they started in Poland,'' Stallings said at a news
conference Friday. ``We want to see these events succeed.
   ``Folks in Washington are scratching their heads trying to
decide how best to respond ... In the meantime, Idahoans are moving
ahead with practical solutions.''
   Morrison Knudsen, a Boise-based engineering, mining and
construction company, agreed to ship the equipment to the East
Coast, where charitable organizations will ship it to Poland,
Stallings said.
</TEXT>
