<FIRST>r a PM-FlagBill     12-15 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Flag Bill,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pa. Lawmaker Proposes $1 Penalty for Beating Flag Burners</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARRISBURG, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A state lawmaker has proposed a $1 fine
for anyone who beats up a person who burns or desecrates American
or state flags.
   Rep. Joseph Petrarca, a Democrat, introduced the legislation
earlier this week.
   The $1 fine would replace the normal penalties for assault or
aggravated assault. A person convicted of aggravated assault could
be sentenced to 10 years in jail and fined $25,000.
   Petrarca said he offered the bill because the House was
unwilling to seek a constitutional amendment to punish flag burners.
   ``Since so many of our neighbors and family members have made
huge sacrifices to protect it on foreign battlefields, sometimes
with their lives, I feel desecrating the flag is a matter to be
taken extremely seriously,'' Petrarca said in a statement.
   The fate of the bill is uncertain.
   ``I can't imagine this is going to go anywhere,'' Rep. Allen
Kukovich, the Democrats' policy chairman, told The Philadelphia
Inquirer. ``But who knows? There are Philistines everywhere, I
guess.''
   Kukovich said such bills ``make the House of Representatives a
laughingstock.''
</TEXT>
