<HEAD>Union Activists Arrested Outside White House</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eighteen trade-union activists were arrested
Friday outside the White House when they blocked a gate during a
peaceful protest over the deaths of labor leaders in El Salvador.
   Maj. William Spruill of the U.S. Park Police said the
demonstrators were charged with demonstrating without a permit, a
misdemeanor. Their permit was revoked when they sat down on the
frigid Pennsylvania Avenue sidewalk and blocked the gate, Spruill
said.
   The protesters, demanding a cutoff of U.S. aid to El Salvador,
said more than 100 trade unionists had been abducted and killed in
a wave of violence that began Oct. 31 with a bombing at the
