criticized for performing at the Grand Ole Opry just after her
husband, country singer Keith Whitley, died from an alcohol
overdose.
   She explained in an interview with the Dallas Times Herald that
the May 9 Opry appearance, the day after her husband's funeral, was
a way to be with friends who could help her through her grief.
