<TEXT>
   The Rev. Joseph Lowery, who heads the civil
rights group founded by the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr., will be
awarded the Martin Luther King, Jr., Nonviolent Peace Prize for
1990.
   ``Dr. Lowery's life and work provide a shining affirmation of
our 1990 King Week theme, `Nonviolence: A Time to Act, A Way to
Live,'' Coretta Scott King, widow of the slain civil-rights leader,
