   Yes Virginia, there really is a
Donald Duck.
   He retired Friday after 21 years as a water meter reader in this
honeymoon capital.
   And what's one of the first things he plans to do in his golden
years?
   Why, go to Disneyland, of course.
   Duck, who turns 65 next month, was born nine years before Walt
Disney introduced his ``wise-quacking'' cartoon character.
   ``I'm the original Donald Duck,'' Duck says matter-of-factly,
recalling a few occasions when his name almost landed him in
trouble, like the time he had to give his name to a traffic cop who
replied: ``Yeah, and I'm Mickey Mouse.''
   Duck's sister wrote Disney to inform him that her brother was
the original Donald Duck, but of a different feather.
   Disney replied with a cartoon sketch autographed: ``To Donald
Duck, from Donald Duck and Walt Disney.''
