<FIRST>r a AM-Mayor'sDaughter     12-15 0216</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mayor's Daughter,0221</SECOND>
<HEAD>LA Mayor's Daughter Booked in Drunken Driving Arrest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mayor Tom Bradley's daughter Phyllis, who has
a history of arrests on drug-related charges and traffic
violations, was held briefly Friday for investigation of drunken
driving.
   Ms. Bradley, 44, refused a sobriety test until after her arrest
and until she had spoken to Bradley, police said. She was arrested
after allegedly making an illegal U-turn, said Sgt. Gary Lynch.
   The arresting officer smelled alcohol on her breath, police
said, but they refused to release the results of the sobriety test
she finally took.
   She received no special treatment and had to wait in line to be
booked at the Wilshire District police station, police said. She
was released about two hours after her arrest after police found
she had no outstanding warrants.
   An arraignment was scheduled Jan. 5 in traffic court.
   ``I was picked up at Pico and Crenshaw for being under the
influence of alcohol,'' Ms. Bradley told reporters after being
released. ``This has happened before.''
   Ms. Bradley's previous run-ins with the law include guilty pleas
to felony counts of driving while under the influence of PCP,
possession of PCP and injuring another person in 1983. She was
placed on probation and ordered to enter a drug rehabilitation
program.
