<FIRST>r w AM-PeanutQuota     12-15 0093</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Peanut Quota,90</SECOND>
<HEAD>Peanut Quota Raised For Next Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Peanut farmers will have a poundage quota of
1.56 million tons in 1990, an increase of 120,000 tons from this
year, the Agriculture Department announced Friday.
   Undersecretary Richard T. Crowder said the department was
required by law to announce next year's peanut quota by Dec. 15.
   Crowder said the national quota will be allocated to each state
based on its share of the 1985 poundage quota. Increases in state
quotas will then be allocated among qualifying peanut farms, he
said.
</TEXT>
