<FIRST>r i AM-Indonesia-Ship     12-15 0111</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Indonesia-Ship,0115</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ship with 75 Aboard Sinks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A wooden ship with 75 people aboard
sank Friday in the Java Sea off Seribu Island, Indonesia's search
and rescue agency said.
   Four aircraft and seven ships looked for survivors from the
33-ton Batam Jaya, said an agency official who spoke on condition
of anonimity.
   The ship, which also was carrying freight, left Sunda Kelapa
port in northern Jakarta on Thursday night for Batam Island in
Riau, the official said.
   The ship sank about 35 miles off the northern coast of Java
Island or about 80 miles northwest of Jakarta.
   Authorities did not know the cause of the accident.
</TEXT>
