<HEAD>Singing Santa Robs Bank</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto PX2</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man wearing a Santa Claus disguise walked
into a suburban bank, gave the teller a note demanding money and
sang softly, ``We wish you a merry Christmas, we wish you a merry
Christmas,'' while he waited.
   The teller gave him more than $1,000, which bank spokesman Paul
Levine called ``just a modest amount.''
   ``The guy spent about 30 minutes in the bank, and he stood in
line until he got to the teller, showed the note and then softly
sang his song,'' FBI spokesman John Kundts said. The FBI did not
say whether he was armed.
   The holdup occurred Dec. 4 in a busy branch of Fidelity Bank in
suburban West Chester. The FBI announced the robbery Friday in
hopes of obtaining information from the public to help solve the
crime.
   A bank surveillance picture showed the costumed Santa wearing
sunglasses and clutching a pocketbook.
