<HEAD>Navy Successfully Drop Tests Rocket Model</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A model rocket was undamaged after being
dropped 1,000 feet from a helicopter into Monterey Bay, Calif., to
see if it could survive high-speed impact with water, the Navy said
Friday.
   The model rocket was traveling at more than 120 mph when it hit
the water in the test Thursday, the Navy said in a statement. Later
tests will involve speeds up to 200 mph.
   The test along the California's central coast was to help
develop a sea launch and recovery rocket that could put a 10,000
pound payload in low earth orbit at a fraction of the cost of
current boosters.
