<TEXT>
   Seven emergency personnel and two others
were overcome by fumes from a high concentration of pesticide
consumed by a man in an apparent suicide attempt Friday,
authorities said.
   The unidentified 35-year-old man who drank the poison was in
critical condition, but the others were treated and released, said
Lodi Memorial Hospital spokeswoman Penny Jacobi.
