<TEXT>
   College graduates in 1990 can look forward to a
job market much like 1989's _ a year of good growth _ with
engineering students pulling in the highest starting salaries,
according to an annual survey.
   But the author of the survey said Thursday the 260 businesses
surveyed were more cautious in their economic outlook than they
were a year ago, with 44 percent saying they expected business to
be about the same and 6 percent predicting a decline. Fifty percent
said they expected a slightly better business climate in 1990.
