but was far outpaced by Japan, the World Bank reported.
   The average per capita income in the United States last year was
$19,780, compared with $18,580 in 1987. In Japan, the average
income rose from $15,840 to $21,040, the World Bank said Friday.
   The Swiss continued to rank first in per capita income with a
1988 average of $27,260, up from $21,310 in 1987.
</TEXT>
