<TEXT>
   Media giant Knight-Ridder Inc. expects to post
higher earnings this year and that savings from its
recently-enacted newspaper joint operating agreement in Detroit
will boost 1990 earnings.
   Tribune Co., meanwhile, said Friday it expects a profit increase
for 1989 but said earnings growth would be more difficult to
achieve in 1990 due to impending labor negotiations, slow
advertising revenue growth and weak newsprint prices.
   New York Times Co. said a gain on the sale of its cable
operations would mean record 1989 earnings, but earnings from
