<TEXT>
   Gillette Co., trying to rebuild profits hurt by
recent takeover battles, has announced it will realign its
operations and sell some of its European business, affecting about
750 workers in the process.
   Gillette said Friday it was creating a North Atlantic Shaving
and Personal Care Group that would encompass its shaving products
and toiletries segments.
