<TEXT>
   Ivan F. Boesky, Wall Street's most notorious
felon, has been permanently released from a federal prison camp and
will serve the rest of his sentence at a Brooklyn halfway house,
authorities said.
   Boesky, 52, was granted the transfer to the halfway house about
10 days ago from the minimum-security Lompoc Federal Prison Camp in
California, where he was imprisoned since March 1988, prison
spokesman Gavin O'Connor said Friday.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A midsession selloff drove stock prices lower Friday amid
